SIMPLE: invite
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Invite
<hw>In*vite"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Invited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Inviting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>invitare</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>inviter</ets>. See <er>Vie</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To ask; to request; to bid; to summon; to ask to do
some act, or go to some place; esp., to ask to an entertainment or
visit; to request the company of; <as>as, to <ex>invite</ex> to dinner,
or a wedding, or an excursion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So many guests <qex>invite</qex> as here are writ.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>invite</qex> his Grace of Castle Rackrent to reflect on
this.</q> <rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To allure; to draw to; to tempt to come; to induce
by pleasure or hope; to attract.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To inveigle and <qex>invite</qex> the unwary sense.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shady groves, that easy sleep <qex>invite</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There no delusive hope <qex>invites</qex> despair.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To give occasion for; <as>as, to <ex>invite</ex>
criticism</as>.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To solicit; bid; call; ask; summon; allure;
attract; entice; persuade.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Invite
<hw>In*vite"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To give invitation.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invitement</ent>⟦br⟧
